<HEADLINE> Today is Presidents Day  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
    	   NEW YORK (AP) - Today is Presidents Day. It is a federal, state and
local holiday in New York, New Jersey and Connecticut.
<P>
	   Here is a list of closings and transit schedules for Monday:
</P>
<P>
	   Federal offices and courts are closed.
</P>
<P>
	   Post offices are closed. There is no regular mail delivery, except for
Express Mail and special delivery; in New York City, the main weigh offices are
open at the James A. Farley building at 33rd Street and 8th Avenue from 8 a.m.
to 9 p.m., and at the Morgan General Mail Facility at 341 9th Avenue from 4 p.m.
to 9 p.m.
</P>
<P>
	   Government offices, banks and financial markets in the United States are
closed today. International financial markets are open. The weekly auction of
Treasury bills will be held Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
	   State offices and courts are closed in New York, New Jersey and Connecticut.
</P>
<P>
	   Government offices and courts are closed in New York City, Westchester,
Rockland, Putnam, Nassau and Suffolk counties;
</P>
<P>
	   New York City public schools are closed. Schools are also closed across the
state; public schools are also closed across Connecticut but public schools have
the option to remain open in New Jersey.
</P>
<P>
	   NEW YORK
</P>
<P>
	   Alternate side-of-the-street parking rules are suspended in New York City;
</P>
<P>
	   There will be no garbage collection and recycling pick-up in New York City,
but no street cleaning;
</P>
<P>
	   New York City subways and buses, Staten Island ferries, the Staten Island
Rapid Transit are running on a regular weekday schedule;
</P>
<P>
	   The Metropolitan Suburban Bus Authority is operating on a regular schedule;
</P>
<P>
	   The Long Island Rail Road and Metro-North commuter railroad are operating on
regular weekday schedules;
</P>
<P>
	   Amtrak is running on its regular schedule;
</P>
<P>
	   Suffolk County Transit buses are operating on a regular weekday schedule;
</P>
<P>
	   Westchester County buses are on a regular weekday schedule;
</P>
<P>
	   Putnam Area Rapid Transit buses are operating on a regular weekday schedule;
</P>
<P>
	   Red and Tan buses serving Rockland and Bergen counties are on a regular
weekday schedule;
</P>
<P>
	   CONNECTICUT
</P>
<P>
	   Connecticut Transit buses in New Haven, Hartford and Stamford are on a
regular weekday schedule;
</P>
<P>
	   The Cross Sound Ferry between New London, Connecticut, and Orient Point,
Long Island, is on a holiday schedule;
</P>
<P>
	   The ferry between Bridgeport, Connecticut, and Port Jefferson, Long Island,
is operating on a Sunday schedule;
</P>
<P>
	   NEW JERSEY
</P>
<P>
	   New Jersey Transit trains will be on a regular schedule. Buses will be on a
regular schedule except for 43 bus routes that will be on a modified schedule in
northern and central New Jersey, and 17 routes that will be on a Saturday
schedule in southern new jersey.
</P>
<P>
	   New Jersey Path trains are operating on a regular weekday schedule.
</P>
