	   The euro was quoted at $0.9873, up from $0.9857 Friday.
</P>
<P>
	   The dollar was worth 111.16 Japanese yen, up from 110.79. Other dollar rates
compared with late Friday: 1.6237 Swiss francs, down from 1.6274; and 1.4508
Canadian dollars, up from 1.4500.
</P>
<P>
	   The British pound was quoted at $1.5995, up from $1.5988.
</P>
<P>
	   Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no longer
traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro rates, the dollar is
worth: 1.9802 German marks, down from 1.9836; 6.6413 French francs, down from
6.6534; 2.2312 Dutch guilders, down from 2.2352; and 1,960.38 Italian lire, down
from 1,963.96
</P>
