<HEADLINE> Dollar Mixed; Gold Higher  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    LONDON (AP) -- The U.S. dollar was mixed against other major currencies in
European trading Monday. Gold prices rose.
</P>
<P>
	   The euro was quoted at $0.9864, up from $0.9857 Friday.
</P>
<P>
	   Other dollar rates compared with late Friday: 111.22 Japanese yen, up from
110.79; 1.6251 Swiss francs, down from 1.6274; and 1.4526 Canadian dollars, up
from 1.4500.
</P>
<P>
	   The British pound was quoted at $1.5992, up from $1.5988.
</P>
<P>
	   U.S. currency markets were closed in observance of Presidents Day.
</P>
<P>
	   Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no longer
traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro rates, the dollar is
worth: 1.9814 German marks, down from 1.9836; 6.6466 French francs, down from
6.6534; 2.2330 Dutch guilders, down from 2.2352; and 1,961.97 Italian lire, down
from 1,963.96
</P>
<P>
	   Gold closed in London at $305.00 bid per troy ounce, up from $302.80 on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
	   In Zurich, the bid price was $304.75, up from $303.75.
</P>
<P>
	   Gold rose $1.50 in Hong Kong to $306.00.
</P>
<P>
	   Silver closed in London at $5.22 bid per troy ounce, down from Friday.
</P>
</TEXT>
