<HEADLINE> Pregnancy Won't Stop Zeta-Jones  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- Despite being pregnant, Catherine Zeta-Jones will still be
able to work on a new film.
</P>
<P>
	   After finding out she was pregnant, Michael Douglas' fiancee had to drop out
of Oliver Stone's movie "Beyond Borders," in which she was to play a war-zone
relief worker who has an affair with a doctor played by Kevin Costner.
</P>
<P>
