<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-21 19:20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cubans March for Elian's Return  </HEADLINE>
   By ANITA SNOW Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
	   HAVANA (AP) -- Shouting ``Free Elian! Down With Lies!'' tens of thousands of
government supporters flooded Havana's coastal highway Monday to demand the
return of the 6-year-old boy and to protest the expulsion of a Cuban diplomat.
</P>
<P>
	   Waving Cuban small flags, uniformed police officers, military cadets,
Foreign Ministry employees and a few top communist officials were among those
called to attended the latest of dozens of rallies and marches held since Dec. 5
to press for Elian Gonzalez's return.
</P>
<P>
	   It was one of the biggest marches yet in 2 1/2 months of demonstrations.
Government officials who carefully organized the march and brought the
protesters to the site in buses, estimated that more than 200,000 people paraded
down the 3 1/2-mile stretch along Havana's Malecon seawall.
</P>
<P>
	   Marchers who streamed past the U.S. Interests Section -- the American
diplomatic mission in Cuba -- were also protesting Washington's decision last
week to expel an unnamed Cuban diplomat. Cuban officials say that announcement
and the related arrest of a U.S. Immigration agent on espionage charges are a
plot to block Elian's return to his homeland.
</P>
<P>
	   ``The clear objective, impossible to hide or overlook, is to prevent at all
cost the return of the kidnapped child,'' read an editorial on the front page of
the Communist Party's workers' weekly, Trabajadores.
</P>
<P>
	   The State Department on Saturday ordered the expulsion of a Cuban diplomat
linked to the Cuban-born U.S. immigration official. The diplomat, whose name was
not released, was given seven days to leave the country.
</P>
<P>
	   The marches began after Elian was rescued off the coast of South Florida on
Nov. 25. Found lashed to an inner tube, the boy was one of only three people who
survived when the boat sank during a journey from Cuba to the United States.
Elian's mother and 10 others perished.
</P>
<P>
	   Elian's father, Juan Miguel Gonzalez, has demanded that the boy be returned
to him in Cuba, and the INS has said that father and son should be reunited.
</P>
<P>
	   The child's Miami relatives are seeking to keep Elian in the United States,
and are seeking political asylum for the boy.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-02-21-00 1920 </TRAILER>
