<HEADLINE> Spike Lee To Appear in Bradley Ad  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Film director Spike Lee will star in a television ad aimed
at helping Bill Bradley come from behind in the Democratic presidential race in
New York.
</P>
<P>
	   ``Sometimes you just got to take the gloves off,'' Lee said Monday. ``It's
for real now. Bill will come out smoking.''
</P>
<P>
	   Lee, who was at the Apollo Theatre for Monday's debate between Bradley and
Vice President Al Gore, said he will star -- but not direct -- the commercial,
which is set to air before New York's March 7 presidential primary. The ad has
not yet been filmed, he said.
</P>
<P>
	   Lee added that he was concerned that black voters are blindly supporting
Gore for the Democratic nomination.
</P>
<P>
	   ``Right or wrong, black people think President Clinton can do no wrong. But
I don't think that means we should automatically transfer that allegiance from
Clinton to Al Gore,'' Lee said.
</P>
<P>
	   Basketball legend Michael Jordan already stars in a Bradley ad.
</P>
