<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-21 21:26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Search finds missing snowmobiler's body  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
    	   MINETTO, N.Y. (AP) - State police have found the body of a 28-year-old
teacher whose snowmobile was found in the icy Oswego River.
<P>
	   Investigators believe Kip L. Kelsey died after he drove along the river
sometime late Saturday or early Sunday as he was returning home after a day of
snowmobiling with friends.
</P>
<P>
	   The body was found Monday evening in 20 feet of water about 300 feet from
shore where his snowmobile was located.
</P>
<P>
	   An autopsy is scheduled for Tuesday to determine the cause of death.
</P>
<P>
	   Sunday morning friends found his helmet on a patch of ice atop the river,
said state police Sgt. Dale R. Crisp. Divers located the snowmobile in the river
Sunday afternoon, he said. A search Sunday was called off when darkness fell.
</P>
<P>
	   Rough terrain along the icy river made the search difficult, Crisp said.
State police used a front-end loader to dump sand over a steep bluff so rescuers
had better footing as they carried down heavy rafts and other equipment, he
said.
</P>
<P>
	   Divers had to fight swift currents, Crisp said.
</P>
<P>
	   The other snowmobilers said they and Kelsey had consumed alcohol on
Saturday, he added.
</P>
<P>
	   Kelsey, who had an infant daughter with his girlfriend, was a popular
technology teacher at Fulton Junior High School, where he taught for the past
five years.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-ES-02-21-00 2126 </TRAILER>
