<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-21 23:34 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Four Killed in Portugal Pileup  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LISBON, Portugal (AP) -- Four people were killed and 70 were injured when
heavy fog along Portugal's main highway caused traffic pileups that involved
about 100 cars, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
	   The collisions occurred 45 miles north of Lisbon on the A1 highway that
links the capital with the northern city of Oporto.
</P>
<P>
	   Traffic along a 20-mile stretch was halted both ways for at least five hours
as 250 rescue officials removed the injured and worked to free up the road,
emergency services spokesman Manuel Laje said.
</P>
<P>
	   Some 6,000 cars were stuck in traffic jams as a result of the accidents,
according to TSF radio.
</P>
<P>
	   The accident believed to have triggered the pileups occurred at 7:30 a.m. in
the North-South direction of the highway because of reduced visibility due to
the fog, Laje said.
</P>
<P>
	   Drivers in the opposite direction slowed down to look at the accidents,
causing further collisions, Laje said.
</P>
</TEXT>
